## Agent skills

This repository ships agent skills at `{{SKILLS_DIR}}/` (also surfaced via
`.claude/skills/` and `.codex/skills/`). At the start of every session, read the
master skill:

    cat {{SKILLS_DIR}}/{{SKILL_CORE}}/SKILL.md

It is the entry point and routes to specialist skills for task workflow, review,
docs sync, diagnosis, and handoff. If you are in an environment without skill
auto-discovery, treat the files under `{{SKILLS_DIR}}/` as required reading
mirroring `{{DOCS_AGENT_DIR}}/*` — the SKILL.md bodies summarize and
`references/` files carry the authoritative source.

## 1. Mission

{{PROJECT_DESC}}

All agent work must preserve:

- Buildability.
- Testability.
- Reviewability of mechanical vs semantic changes.
- Documentation synchronization.

## 2. Operating principles

- Keep patches small and scoped to one task whenever possible.
- Do not mix mechanical moves/renames with semantic refactors.
- Prefer deterministic, testable APIs with explicit ownership and failure states.
- Match the conventions, naming, and comment density of the surrounding code.
- Leave the tree at least as green as you found it.

